e_burnout_A_guide_for_leaders_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_15191132-debc-41ae-889f-fec4a45e7737_500x.png?v=1692184279 320w" width="1474" height="982" alt="Navigating employee burnout A guide for leaders - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Navigating employee burnout A guide for leaders - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-15_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-8b93" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jNHqnW kXSKNz pf-16_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-cqJhZP gRKDwp"><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-17_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eySxxw fIKYYX pf-18_"><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-19_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-21_">How do you respond to employee burnout? Are you comfortable responding to concerns about burnout within your team? Although there are many articles about workplace burnout, there needs to be comprehensive guidance for managers and leaders.<br><br>The silent spectre of employee burnout looms in today's high-stakes global business environment. Burnout contributes significantly to a talent shortage that presents costly and complex challenges affecting millions across every sector and industry. In a startling revelation, an estimated 100 million employees worldwide left their jobs in 2022, with burnout often cited as a primary driver.<br><br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> explores effective leadership strategies when faced with an employee expressing burnout.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-24_">Taking employee burnout seriously: Establishing a culture of empathy 
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Taking_employee_burnout_seriously_Establishing_a_culture_of_empathy_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096193" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Taking_employee_burnout_seriously_Establishing_a_culture_of_empathy_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096193 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Taking_employee_burnout_seriously_Establishing_a_culture_of_empathy_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692096193 320w" width="1984" height="1323" alt="Taking employee burnout seriously Establishing a culture of empathy - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Taking employee burnout seriously Establishing a culture of empathy - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-28_">One of the initial challenges managers face when an employee opens up about burnout is to resist the temptation to dismiss or downplay their concerns. It's easy to assume the employee is merely overwhelmed or lacks resilience. However, it's critical to treat their concerns with gravity regardless of whether or not their experience meets the clinical definition of burnout. Establishing a culture of empathy by scheduling a dedicated, one-on-one conversation signals your commitment to their well-being. It can help forge a stronger bond of trust between you and the employee.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-31_">Understanding the employee's experience of burnout: The diagnostic trifecta
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_the_employee_s_experience_of_burnout_The_diagnostic_trifecta_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096266" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_the_employee_s_experience_of_burnout_The_diagnostic_trifecta_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096266 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_the_employee_s_experience_of_burnout_The_diagnostic_trifecta_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692096266 320w" width="1752" height="1168" alt="Understanding the employee's experience of burnout The diagnostic trifecta - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understanding the employee's experience of burnout The diagnostic trifecta - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-32_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-35_">Distinguishing between temporary stress and actual burnout can be a challenging task. To make this process easier, there are three pivotal questions leaders can pose to their employees:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eZhRLC dwDNfh pf-36_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-37_"><b>"Do you feel competent and effective in your job?"</b> - This question offers insight into the employee's self-perception of efficacy and job performance, providing clues as to whether they could benefit from additional support or training.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-39_"><b>"Do you feel emotionally exhausted in your job and/or experience physical symptoms?"</b> - This question probes negative emotions, fatigue, and physical health symptoms such as stress-related headaches or anxiety, often prevalent in burnout.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dYtuZ fhpFsJ pf-41_"><b>"Do you find yourself feeling cynical or caring less than you used to about your colleagues or clients?"</b> - This question helps detect changes in the employee's work-related attitudes, capturing potential shifts from dedication to cynicism.</li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-45_">Identifying the root causes of burnout: Unearthing the stressors
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identifying_the_root_causes_of_burnout_Unearthing_the_stressors_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096580" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identifying_the_root_causes_of_burnout_Unearthing_the_stressors_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096580 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Identifying_the_root_causes_of_burnout_Unearthing_the_stressors_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692096580 320w" width="1260" height="840" alt="Identifying the root causes of burnout Unearthing the stressors - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Identifying the root causes of burnout Unearthing the stressors - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-46_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-49_">The journey to addressing burnout effectively must pass through the valley of its root causes. Managers must discuss the significant stressors in the employee's life. These can originate from outside work, like financial stress or caregiving responsibilities, or from within the workplace, such as an imbalance between work demands and available resources.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-50_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-52_">Considering immediate and long-term solutions: A two-tiered approach
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Considering_immediate_and_long-term_solutions_A_two-tiered_approach_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096643" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Considering_immediate_and_long-term_solutions_A_two-tiered_approach_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096643 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Considering_immediate_and_long-term_solutions_A_two-tiered_approach_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692096643 320w" width="1752" height="1168" alt="Considering immediate and long-term solutions A two-tiered approach - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Considering immediate and long-term solutions A two-tiered approach - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-53_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-54_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Once you understand the causes of an employee's burnout, it's time to consider appropriate responses. The solutions should comprise immediate measures to alleviate current distress and long-term strategies to prevent recurrence. Immediate solutions include delegating some of their workloads, renegotiating deadlines, or offering time off. Longer-term strategies involve adjusting job responsibilities, providing more flexibility in how and where they work, or investing in their personal and professional development.<br> 
</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-56_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-58_">Creating a monitoring plan: Sustaining change over time
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Creating_a_monitoring_plan_Sustaining_change_over_time_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096766" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Creating_a_monitoring_plan_Sustaining_change_over_time_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1692096766 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Creating_a_monitoring_plan_Sustaining_change_over_time_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1692096766 320w" width="1125" height="750" alt="Creating a monitoring plan Sustaining change over time - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Creating a monitoring plan Sustaining change over time - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-59_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-60_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Eradicating burnout isn't a task with a definitive end point but requires ongoing effort and engagement. Regular check-ins with the employee can help monitor progress, adjust strategies as needed, and reaffirm your commitment to their well-being. By following these steps, leaders can build an empathetic, supportive environment that effectively addresses burnout and fosters retention.<br> 
</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-62_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-64_">Key points to remember
